        "id": "noscope-2wn",
        "title": "Multiple credentials per invocation",
        "description": "Provenance REQ: jn78wxpmbj1kegw5c8qv05nmzn83tbgd\n\nReal agent tasks need credentials from multiple services. Each provider mints independently with its own env_key. If one fails, revoke all successfully minted and exit error. Concurrent minting for performance.\n\nRules:\n- NS-006: Atomic multi-credential minting — if any provider fails, revoke all minted, exit error; no partial credential sets\n- NS-045: Env key uniqueness — reject credential sets with duplicate env_key; validate before minting; identify conflicting providers\n- NS-046: Parallel minting timeout — per-provider timeout (default 30s); exceed triggers atomic rollback per NS-006\n- NS-047: Atomic rollback follows revocation budget — same timeout/retry policy as signal-triggered revocation (NS-027); log failure with credential ID+TTL\n- NS-048: Independent refresh scheduling — each credential has own refresh timer based on its TTL/expires_at; no sync/batching\n- NS-049: Single credential expiry preserves child — one expired does not terminate child; log warning; do not re-mint\n- NS-050: Bounded parallelism for provider operations — configurable max concurrent (default 8); prevents FD exhaustion/rate limits\n\nProvenance stats: 0 resolutions, 7 rules",
