        "title": "CLI: provider discovery and configuration",
        "description": "Provenance REQ: jn72kkrbwj1gk2k10zxsqz13d583vws2\n\nCLI binary: noscope --provider \u003cname\u003e --role \u003crole\u003e --ttl \u003cduration\u003e -- \u003ccommand\u003e. Provider config at ~/.config/noscope/providers/\u003cname\u003e.toml. Fallback to env vars (NOSCOPE_MINT_CMD etc.) or inline flags (--mint-cmd).\n\nRules:\n- NS-007: Strict config precedence — flags \u003e env vars \u003e config files; no merging across layers; highest-precedence wins entirely\n- NS-042: Config follows XDG Base Directory — XDG_CONFIG_HOME/noscope/ default ~/.config/noscope/; providers/\u003cname\u003e.toml, profiles/\u003cname\u003e.toml\n- NS-043: Malformed config is hard error — syntactically invalid or missing required fields = exit error; never silently fall through; missing file = layer absent, not error\n- NS-044: Provider not found enumerates checked locations — print file path, env var name, flag name checked at each layer; sufficient for user diagnosis\n- NS-069: Config file permission enforcement — reject world-readable files (must be 0600 or 0640 on Unix)\n- NS-071: Dry-run mode — --dry-run validates config, resolves provider, prints commands with substituted vars; no real minting\n- NS-073: Provider validation command — noscope validate --provider \u003cname\u003e verifies mint command exists+executable, config well-formed; no real credentials\n\nProvenance stats: 1 resolution, 7 rules",
