        "title": "Process group management (PR_SET_PDEATHSIG)",
        "description": "Provenance REQ: jn70zc9m0vfsxrwv8smne7kxt583vnwz\n\nPR_SET_PDEATHSIG set on child before exec ensures child receives SIGTERM if noscope dies (SIGKILL, crash, OOM). Process group kill on exit ensures grandchildren are also terminated. Linux-specific, defense-in-depth on top of TTL. Does not apply to mint mode.\n\nRules:\n- NS-024: Process group management in run mode — PR_SET_PDEATHSIG on child; create new process group; kill entire group on exit; prevents orphaned grandchildren retaining credentials\n\nProvenance stats: 0 resolutions, 1 rule",
        "notes": "Provenance sync (2026-03-29):\n- Requirement anchors: jn76esa0pkmnsd7s4y5m5ft36s83tkh7 (lifecycle) and jn764cw67wc4h6d9st0qpe903x83vbgz (signal policy).\n- New audit source link: k1716vskd1q7gm1kgfmc9053yh83tfx9.\n- Execution sequencing follows resolution js7753pmggjn1kh9xqf9929czh83tha1.\nAGENT NOTE: Do NOT attempt to read /proc/self/* or any /proc paths. The sandbox will reject external directory access and crash your session. Work from libc documentation and man page knowledge (prctl(2), setpgid(2), kill(2)) instead. All implementation should be policy types and cfg(target_os) abstractions -- no runtime /proc access needed.",
