    "id": "noscope-508",
    "title": "AgentProcess: spawn, lifecycle, exit code passthrough",
    "description": "Provenance REQ: jn76esa0pkmnsd7s4y5m5ft36s83tkh7\n\nAgentProcess struct: spawn with credential injection, signal forwarding to child, exit code passthrough, revoke-on-exit guarantee. Process must exit with child's exit code, not noscope's.\n\nRules:\n- NS-002: Exit code passthrough — exit with child's exit code, transparent in pipelines\n- NS-013: Stdout belongs to child or mint output — run mode: no stdout from noscope; mint mode: only token JSON; all diagnostics to stderr\n- NS-021: Strip noscope config from child environment — remove all NOSCOPE_* env vars before spawn\n- NS-022: Env var collision is fatal error — if target env_key already set, exit with error; --force to override\n- NS-023: Signal-killed child exit code convention — 128+signal_number (POSIX); 127=not found, 126=permission denied\n- NS-057: Global wall-clock timeout — --timeout for total lifecycle, kill child + revoke on exceed\n\nProvenance stats: 2 resolutions, 6 rules",
